    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the roasted veg is tender, heat a large, wide-based pot over a high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong> with the <strong>roasted veg</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>,<strong> </strong>700ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and the <strong>coriander</strong> (save some leaves for garnish!) then bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, remove the pot from the heat and use a <strong>(stick) blender </strong>(or add to a food processor) to blitz until smooth, then return to a low heat to keep warm – this is your <strong>Thai-style sweet potato soup</strong></p>",
